  "name": "RPlog_A_Bit_Of_A_Situation",
  "title": "A Bit of a Situation at the Smuggler's Dig",
  "summary": "In the squalid cantina known as the Smuggler's Dig, the pirate Captain Jalek trades philosophy and barbs with the pirate fighter pilot Talia over drinks, his glib talk of freedom interrupted when CorSec Colonel Twila, a Twi'lek, enters to work in peace. Jalek cannot resist needling Twila about her absent human lover Gren, goading her until she strips off her belt and swings at him; he counters with drunken grace, pins her against the bar, and ultimately cuffs her at blasterpoint while his anxious clerk Pyat looks on and a crowd of Aqualish bookmakers takes wild bets on the outcome. Talia, refusing to get involved, draws her own weapon when she catches Jalek whispering for Twila to 'play along,' and the standoff teeters toward a brawl. The retired CorSec inspector turned Sith Tyler Damion then strides in, ignites a white lightsaber, frees Twila by force, and orders Jalek to release her, declaring the captain himself responsible for cleaning up the chaos. As a full bar brawl erupts among the gamblers, Tyler calmly deactivates his blade and retreats to a fresh bottle of rum, leaving Jalek to face the mess he has made.",
